There is a wide selection of plants suitable for growing at wintertime. These include:Lamb's lettuce (Valerianella locusta) - this is also known as corn salad. It is a very popular salad green in Europe, where it is also known as mache. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/66/Grow-Winter-Salads-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Grow-Winter-Salads-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/66/Grow-Winter-Salads-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Grow-Winter-Salads-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Cos lettuces are a good choice - look for miniature varieties if you are growing indoors, as well as the heirloom varieties such as "Rouge d'hiver". {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/bb/Grow-Winter-Salads-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Grow-Winter-Salads-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/bb/Grow-Winter-Salads-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Grow-Winter-Salads-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Chicory - this is a slightly bitter salad green that adds life to a winter salad. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/aa/Grow-Winter-Salads-Step-2Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Grow-Winter-Salads-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/aa/Grow-Winter-Salads-Step-2Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Grow-Winter-Salads-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
